snippet.textDisplay: Anybody who know anything about boxing, or has followed the sport for a while, knew that Helenius was a HUGE step up for Kownacki. Now Helenius, has been a bit of an underachiever, and somewhat of a disappointment from what he was heralded to be...but he was 50x better than anybody Kownacki has faced. Add to that, he's a really big guy who can punch. Helenius being that big of an underdog was laughable, and this is not that big of an upset, if you knew what you were looking at.
